Luego de generar el dist del proyecto angular, podemos usar este dist en un servidor web existen o para pruebas instalar un servidor http:
    npm i -g http-server --save

Para desplegar el dist con el http-server instalado:
    http-server ./dist

****************************************************************

To create a new project:
-> ng new my-app

To resolve atom editor warning after installing plugins:
-> https://stackoverflow.com/questions/49699157/atom-and-boostrap-4-failed-to-load-snippet-duplicate-key-button-group-boots

To start the angular application (to open in web browser you can use --open)
Similar to spring boot: angular has it own embedded server to deploy the application.
This command "ng serve" should be used only in development environment (not for production)
For production environment we should convert all the typescript code to pure static code (html/javascript).
-> ng serve --open

To generate automatically the component (html, spec.ts, ts and css), this update automatically
the app.module.ts including the new component:
-> ng generate component <<component-name>>

To generate model class:
-> ng generate class <<class-name>>

With typescript >= 2.7 add the following property in tsconfig.json after "strict": true
-> "strictPropertyInitialization": false

To generate service component:
-> ng generate service <<service-name>>

To download all dependencies:
-> npm install

To compile and generate dist:
-> ng build --prod

To deploy in firebase al dist content should be moved into new "public" directory

To install firebase tools (similar to heroku cli):
-> npm install -g firebase-tools

